                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@dilger.ca&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9670dabd-cedc-4215-b787-f6b43b4bf7fb&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/9670dabd-cedc-4215-b787-f6b43b4bf7fb&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_224 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;FAIL: tcp should be down
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/122121&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/122121&lt;/a&gt; - 5.15.0-142-generic&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/122121&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-reviews/122121&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-553.89.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like this is failing intermittently, maybe once per month, with the most recent failure with this message was on 2025-12-04.  There were a number of failures on 2025-11-01 testing patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/62158&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/62158&lt;/a&gt; (&quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12597&quot; title=&quot;test-framework mdts_nodes, osts_nodes should return comma_list&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12597&quot;&gt;LU-12597&lt;/a&gt; tests: remove comma_list for nodes_list&quot;), but that patch did not land yet and had a different error message.&lt;/p&gt;






&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
sanity-lnet test_224 - tcp should be down&lt;/p&gt;</description>
